items.caption_text:
List of recyclers in India below👇🏻

Littering has become so normal that we don’t even notice it anymore. And slowly… small landfills are forming right outside our homes.

Not the big government ones we see in documentaries but mini dumping sites in our own neighborhoods. Corners of streets. Vacant plots. Road dividers. Construction sites.

We complain about pollution.
But we ignore the pile growing 200 meters from our house.

The truth?
Most of what we throw “away” doesn’t go away. It just relocates.

Plastic wrappers, cardboard boxes, multilayered packaging so much of it can be recycled if we segregate and send it to the right place.

For the past few months, I’ve been collecting my dry waste separately and sending it to recyclers instead of letting it mix and end up in landfill. And the difference it makes is huge.

If each of us stopped treating waste like it’s someone else’s responsibility, these micro-landfills wouldn’t exist.

Ready to be part of the recycling revolution? ♻️

